Allow version-specific patching of stable kernels

From: Shung-Hsi Yu <shung-hsi.yu@suse.com>

The version specific patch would live in separate directly under
ci/diffs, e.g.:
- /ci/diffs/6.12
- /ci/diffs/6.6

Use `format()` instead of direct string interpolation otherwise the
conditional will not work as intended, and we get the following warning:

  Conditional expression contains literal text outside replacement
  tokens. This will cause the expression to always evaluate to truthy.
  Did you mean to put the entire expression inside ${{ }}?

Signed-off-by: Shung-Hsi Yu <shung-hsi.yu@suse.com>
---
 .github/workflows/vmtest-stable.yml |    8 ++++++++
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+)

diff --git a/.github/workflows/vmtest-stable.yml b/.github/workflows/vmtest-stable.yml
index bdbdbe0..f9e151b 100644
--- a/.github/workflows/vmtest-stable.yml
+++ b/.github/workflows/vmtest-stable.yml
@@ -77,6 +77,14 @@ jobs:
           	fi
           done
 
+      - name: Patch kernel source (specific)
+        uses: libbpf/ci/patch-kernel@v3
+        # Only run when the kernel-specific directory exists
+        if: hashFiles(format('ci/diffs/{0}/**', inputs.kernel)) != ''
+        with:
+          patches-root: '${{ github.workspace }}/ci/diffs/${{ inputs.kernel }}/'
+          repo-root: '.kernel'
+
       - name: Patch kernel source
         uses: libbpf/ci/patch-kernel@v3
